        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(reply): hoist direct-send fragment index",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFinal reply payload processing rebuilt the directly-sent assistant fragment index inside every payload check. Multi-payload replies therefore rescanned all streamed block payloads repeatedly.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe fragment map is now built once per reply-payload collection and reused by the direct-send predicate. Matching, metadata scoping, and media handling are unchanged.\n\n## User Impact\n\nReplies with many streamed payloads spend less CPU in duplicate suppression and direct-send preservation.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Focused tests: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-payloads.test.ts`\n- Result: 65 tests passed.\n- Fresh autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n- Rebased source commit: `914810b2bc`\n",
